title: Jammie Deese
text: Jammie Deese (born May 10, 1977) is an <a href="American%20football">American football</a> coach and former <a href="American%20football">American football</a> <a href="wide%20receiver">wide receiver</a>. He played <a href="college%20football">college football</a> for the <a href="Wake%20Forest%20Demon%20Deacons%20football">Wake Forest Demon Deacons</a>, then played professionally for the <a href="Carolina%20Cobras">Carolina Cobras</a> in the <a href="Arena%20Football%20League">Arena Football League</a> and <a href="Fayetteville%20Guard">Fayetteville Guard</a> in the <a href="National%20Indoor%20Football%20League">National Indoor Football League</a>. From 2016 to 2019, he was the <a href="offensive%20coordinator">offensive coordinator</a> for the <a href="college%20football">college football</a> program at <a href="West%20Florida%20Argonauts%20football">West Florida</a>, helping them win a Division II national championship in 2019. Since 2020, he has been the head coach at Forest Hills High School in <a href="Marshville%2C%20North%20Carolina">Marshville, North Carolina</a>.
